WEBVTT

00:00.174 --> 00:05.122
♪ Hey, why is it happening ♪

00:06.094 --> 00:08.802
♪ My heart is racing ♪

00:09.934 --> 00:13.942
♪ The world has fallen silent ♪

00:13.966 --> 00:18.722
♪ Hey, when I imagine you ♪

00:19.758 --> 00:22.786
♪ What kind of look ♪

00:23.790 --> 00:27.734
♪ Attracted me to you ♪

00:27.758 --> 00:31.030
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:31.054 --> 00:34.518
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:34.542 --> 00:39.790
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:39.790 --> 00:41.408
♪ I love you ♪

00:41.408 --> 00:44.886
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:44.910 --> 00:48.182
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:48.206 --> 00:53.878
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:53.902 --> 00:55.246
♪ I love you ♪

00:55.246 --> 00:58.582
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:58.606 --> 01:01.954
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:02.062 --> 01:07.259
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:07.259 --> 01:08.942
♪ I love you ♪

01:08.942 --> 01:12.342
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

01:12.366 --> 01:15.766
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:15.790 --> 01:21.366
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:21.390 --> 01:24.802
♪ I love you ♪

01:27.080 --> 01:27.870
=Love Me, Love My Voice=

01:27.870 --> 01:31.218
=Love Me, Love My Voice=
=Episode 18=

01:32.382 --> 01:34.032
(Sudden wedding fever.)

01:42.193 --> 01:47.453
I was just thinking
our audience feedback was so positive,

01:47.453 --> 01:51.390
so I asked you for something exciting,
but you ended up just hugging her.

01:51.390 --> 01:52.474
I found it very disappointing.

01:52.474 --> 01:56.194
You wasted a 24-hour live broadcast.

01:56.194 --> 02:00.954
I'm a cosplayer, but my voice is hoarser
than those of you voice actors.

02:00.954 --> 02:04.534
Don't you know him? Mr. Qiang has
a sharp tongue but he's thin-skinned.

02:04.534 --> 02:09.394
Be patient. Mr. Qiang will do something
more exciting once he gets off.

02:09.394 --> 02:10.913
- Really?
- Is it true?

02:10.913 --> 02:12.306
Right.

02:13.073 --> 02:17.054
- Is it true, Sheng?
- Sheng has thin skin. Please help her.

02:17.913 --> 02:22.854
Stop. Sheng is a girl. You guys
can't talk about her like that, right?

02:22.854 --> 02:27.314
Right. Watch your words. You guys
have so many fans. Be serious.

02:27.314 --> 02:29.554
- Don't you know any better?
- Right.

02:29.554 --> 02:31.994
Sheng is from our singer department.
How could you behave like this?

02:31.994 --> 02:34.394
- Right, it's you.
- We're really disappointed in you.

02:34.394 --> 02:38.054
You were really bold tonight,
even saying Sheng was your girl.

02:39.353 --> 02:41.654
Your throat is better?

02:42.353 --> 02:45.973
- No, I'm gonna drink some water.
- Drink a lot.

02:48.633 --> 02:50.866
- Don't worry.
- Thanks.

02:51.422 --> 02:52.978
N-Not at all.

02:54.874 --> 03:01.734
- Did you ever see a dubbed play before?
- No, it was my first time.

03:01.734 --> 03:08.853
- What do you think?
- Quite stunning. I'm still excited.

03:10.353 --> 03:14.494
Really? I didn't manage
to play to my full strength.

03:16.434 --> 03:20.214
They just love to joke around.
The best solution is to ignore them.

03:20.214 --> 03:23.293
Otherwise, once I respond,
they'll never stop.

03:26.033 --> 03:27.033
Are you tired?

03:27.674 --> 03:30.894
Singing was not tiring,
but being nervous exhausted me.

03:39.234 --> 03:43.334
- Really angry? Why?
- Being petty, aren't you?

04:02.994 --> 04:07.654
The estimated number was 3,000,000.
Tonight, it was over 20,000,000!

04:07.654 --> 04:12.034
- The Perfect Voice is too awesome.
- Not sleeping yet? It's about time.

04:12.034 --> 04:17.374
Don't I have to write a report? Anyway,
I'm still excited and can't sleep.

04:20.034 --> 04:22.734
Once I finish writing,
we can let loose and enjoy ourselves.

04:29.585 --> 04:31.045
It's about time to leave.

04:57.545 --> 04:58.845
What's on your mind?

05:00.225 --> 05:02.085
I'm sleepy. I woke up too early.

05:03.345 --> 05:07.525
I'm used to it. I often get up
at 5 AM or 6 AM for the early shift.

05:10.665 --> 05:15.405
Mr. Zhu, where are we going today?
Why don't you introduce it?

05:15.405 --> 05:16.684
Okay.

05:17.504 --> 05:21.444
Today, everyone will visit
the Longji Rice Terraces, our last stop.

05:23.064 --> 05:27.324
What's wrong with you? You seem to be
in a low mood and a bit sentimental.

05:28.465 --> 05:35.045
- Do you want eye drops for a good cry?
- Stop. I didn't rest well yesterday.

05:40.384 --> 05:44.024
With such a good response, it'll be
easier to get sponsors next time.

05:44.024 --> 05:49.202
You can start planning the next play
once we leave tomorrow.

05:49.630 --> 05:51.865
- Deal?
- Yes. Deal.

05:51.865 --> 05:54.985
He's the hardest to ask. He said yes.
It means our studio said yes.

05:54.985 --> 05:56.305
- Right.
- Right.

05:56.305 --> 05:57.364
I'll join too.

05:58.105 --> 05:59.285
Okay.

05:59.864 --> 06:01.765
- A better mood now.
- You're brightened.

06:01.765 --> 06:06.424
Mr. Zhu, you're the best. So,
where are we going finally today?

06:06.424 --> 06:08.485
- Isn't it time for an introduction?
- Do introduce it.

06:08.485 --> 06:12.445
- Stand up, professional guide.
- Come on.

06:12.445 --> 06:19.405
Our last stop is Longji Rice Terraces,
a national 4A-level scenic area.

06:19.405 --> 06:23.844
- Wow!
- Stunning views and a pleasant climate.

06:23.844 --> 06:27.230
A lush green expanse, so beautiful.
Seriously, you all need to take a look.

06:27.230 --> 06:30.344
I really suggest you buy
a house there if you can.

06:30.344 --> 06:34.405
Stop. You are not taking us
to appreciate the Longji Rice Terraces.

06:34.405 --> 06:37.225
- You're urging us to buy land there.
- Exactly.

06:37.225 --> 06:38.665
- We should buy land,
- We will.

06:38.665 --> 06:40.624
- since it's Mr. Zhu's order.
- Mr. Zhu, why don't you buy

06:40.624 --> 06:43.944
- a house big enough to hold us all?
- Who has so much money?

06:43.944 --> 06:45.924
- So what? You must.
- Is that what you mean?

06:46.665 --> 06:48.205
Just buy one.

06:49.598 --> 06:52.318
♪ Dreams await at the start
of our encounter ♪

06:52.318 --> 06:54.482
♪ Touching the fingertips ♪

06:55.262 --> 06:58.340
♪ Longing for the world in your eyes ♪

06:58.340 --> 07:01.121
♪ The unspoken understanding
reflects in our gaze ♪

07:01.145 --> 07:04.085
Come on, everyone.

07:04.824 --> 07:06.124
Beautiful, isn't it?

07:07.326 --> 07:09.938
♪ I want to go with you ♪

07:10.905 --> 07:14.764
- It looks the best from this angle.
- Beautiful, isn't it?

07:15.465 --> 07:17.344
- The air is really good.
- There is an echo.

07:17.344 --> 07:20.884
- It would be even prettier without fog.
- Look over there.

07:21.598 --> 07:25.286
♪ Looking up,
chasing the momentary fireworks ♪

07:25.310 --> 07:26.719
♪ Falling in the midst of summer ♪

07:26.719 --> 07:29.630
♪ Every moment of falling in love ♪

07:29.630 --> 07:32.146
♪ Let it blossom ♪

07:40.384 --> 07:42.444
- Let's take a picture.
- Sheng, Doudou.

07:42.444 --> 07:45.584
They're taking photos
in ethnic costumes. So pretty.

07:45.584 --> 07:46.945
Let's go rent ones too.

07:46.945 --> 07:49.285
- Sure. Where is it?
- I saw it on the way.

07:49.285 --> 07:52.244
There are Miao and Zhuang costumes.
Let's each pick one to take photos.

07:52.244 --> 07:53.345
- Alright.
- Wait for a moment.

07:53.345 --> 07:54.645
Let's head there, Sheng.

08:04.824 --> 08:09.444
- Make me look better on the camera.
- How do you feel when it's almost over?

08:10.384 --> 08:11.684
My feelings.

08:14.424 --> 08:21.165
- I have a sudden wedding fever.
- Are you not afraid of scaring her?

08:27.864 --> 08:33.325
- What do you think? Am I pretty?
- Amazing. I almost don't recognize you.

08:45.985 --> 08:47.825
- Take it.
- I will take photos for you.

08:47.825 --> 08:49.485
Do I look good?

08:53.585 --> 08:54.605
Yes.

08:57.065 --> 09:02.525
- What do the locals wear for weddings?
- I didn't ask. Do you want to rent one?

09:02.525 --> 09:07.845
I'm single. I'm asking for someone.

09:13.225 --> 09:16.124
- Let's go there to take some photos.
- Okay.

09:17.904 --> 09:20.425
- They're leaving.
- They're shy.

09:20.425 --> 09:23.464
- Forget them. Let's continue. Come on.
- Come on.

09:23.464 --> 09:25.374
- Come join us.
- Together.

09:25.374 --> 09:27.225
- You hold this.
- Okay. The four of us together.

09:27.225 --> 09:28.644
- Come on.
- Come on.

09:29.904 --> 09:32.364
- Give me your phone.
- Okay.

09:37.744 --> 09:39.114
Are you ready?

09:39.114 --> 09:41.085
One, two, three.

09:42.985 --> 09:45.364
One, two, three.

09:47.264 --> 09:49.124
One, two, three.

09:57.105 --> 10:00.725
- What are you looking at?
- Watch your step. Many steps.

10:04.624 --> 10:06.845
Slow down. Walk behind me.

10:08.065 --> 10:11.764
- Why should I walk behind?
- The steps are too narrow.

10:11.764 --> 10:16.205
If you slip, I'm ahead
to stop you from rolling down.

10:23.624 --> 10:26.845
I can't see the end at all.
How much longer do we have to walk?

10:27.945 --> 10:29.124
Take it slow.

10:29.864 --> 10:31.805
There's no rush anyway.

10:32.664 --> 10:35.644
Normally, work is crazy busy.

10:36.225 --> 10:39.605
It's rare to not be in a hurry
and to walk slowly like this.

10:45.504 --> 10:48.044
Slow down. The ground is slippery.

10:48.664 --> 10:51.525
If I were your girlfriend,
I'd be annoyed by your dawdling.

10:51.525 --> 10:53.054
Safety is a priority.

10:53.054 --> 10:56.145
If you fall, your shoes will get wet,
and your trousers will be damaged.

10:56.145 --> 11:01.724
- You'll have to pay for the clothes.
- Yes, you're absolutely right.

11:01.724 --> 11:09.685
- Can we still get down before dusk?
- I'm doing this for your own good.

11:09.685 --> 11:15.805
- You're older but more reckless.
- Do you have to emphasize my age?

11:15.805 --> 11:21.704
Yes. When you want to curse me,
remember to be kind to the young.

11:21.704 --> 11:25.965
When did I curse you?
Tell me when I cursed you.

11:26.864 --> 11:29.404
- Let's go. You're blocking the way.
- I...

11:31.105 --> 11:34.845
- Slow down. You stepped on my skirt.
- You told me not to dawdle. Let's go.

11:37.345 --> 11:38.445
Slow down.

11:41.225 --> 11:44.904
- So beautiful.
- I'll hold you ahead. Walk slowly.

11:44.904 --> 11:47.584
Why are you two changing places?
For fun?

11:47.584 --> 11:50.704
You don't get it.
He's caring for his girlfriend.

11:50.704 --> 11:54.745
You could never be
as considerate as Mr. Qiang.

11:54.745 --> 11:57.225
I say one thing and here comes lectures.

11:57.225 --> 12:00.584
Because I'm angry. Without you,
I would have arrived before them.

12:00.584 --> 12:05.885
All my effort protecting you
was in vain. My hand is all stiff now.

12:05.885 --> 12:10.165
What do you want? Let me massage it.
Mr. Feng, you've worked hard.

12:10.165 --> 12:13.524
Be cautious. Don't fall.

12:20.985 --> 12:22.685
Underneath is firewood.

12:23.504 --> 12:28.764
Have you noticed underneath the houses
we've come across are all woodsheds?

12:29.585 --> 12:32.965
The overall area is damp.
The first floor is not habitable.

12:34.825 --> 12:37.845
What took you so long?
Do you want something to drink?

12:38.945 --> 12:42.125
- Do you want?
- No, thank you. I won't drink.

12:42.125 --> 12:44.404
- Let's take a break.
- Okay.

12:51.504 --> 12:54.164
It's time to go back.
I'm reluctant to leave.

12:56.734 --> 12:58.226
What can't you part with?

12:58.825 --> 13:03.794
The beer fish,
the spotted fish or the oil tea?

13:04.446 --> 13:05.884
All of them.

13:06.664 --> 13:09.164
And the hundred thousand green hills.

13:09.744 --> 13:13.004
How do they reckon there are
a hundred thousand green hills?

13:15.144 --> 13:16.644
They stretch unbroken.

13:17.425 --> 13:18.965
It's over a hundred thousand.

13:19.544 --> 13:25.618
- You've searched it?
- Days ago, I recorded an audiobook.

13:26.142 --> 13:30.645
It tells of a revolutionary general
from Guilin during the warlord era.

13:30.645 --> 13:36.124
He fought a lot, battling warlords
and resisting the Japan's Army.

13:37.744 --> 13:39.764
But in the end, he didn't return here.

13:41.945 --> 13:43.965
This is his mother's hometown.

13:44.864 --> 13:50.605
The place where he grew up.
He mentioned the green hills

13:51.345 --> 13:52.946
and Lijiang River many times.

13:54.024 --> 13:56.044
People of that era

13:56.784 --> 13:58.164
are admirable.

13:59.504 --> 14:02.764
You make me want
to write a song so badly.

14:05.185 --> 14:10.004
I'm getting busier and busier
and hardly have time for recording.

14:10.864 --> 14:15.244
However, I still keep recording
audiobooks as it forces me to read.

14:15.904 --> 14:21.185
Moreover, I've enjoyed listening to
audiobooks alone since childhood.

14:21.185 --> 14:27.244
Then, when I started recording,
I felt that listening to audiobooks

14:28.985 --> 14:31.524
was like accompanying real persons.

14:38.105 --> 14:41.364
I suddenly found
this type of clothing is quite nice.

14:42.705 --> 14:47.645
At home, as long as you hear
the sound from the clothes,

14:47.645 --> 14:51.925
you know someone's back
and it's time to cook.

14:53.624 --> 14:57.884
What if a group of girls
pass by the house?

14:59.225 --> 15:01.124
Then,

15:03.264 --> 15:06.325
I'll add a few more bells
to your necklace.

15:08.024 --> 15:09.565
Different from others.

15:11.864 --> 15:15.665
Qiang Qingci will use up
all his sweet talk on Shengshengman.

15:15.665 --> 15:19.464
- Isn't that how it should be?
- Aren't you over the constant dissing?

15:19.464 --> 15:23.084
You guys always gang up on Qiang Qingci.

15:23.084 --> 15:26.145
- I didn't go that far.
- I...

15:26.145 --> 15:31.164
Mu is an expert at dissing people,
so I never provoke him.

15:35.784 --> 15:39.665
We only have time to visit this place.
Next time, you can...

15:39.665 --> 15:41.985
- They're back.
- They're back.

15:41.985 --> 15:44.178
- They're back.
- Looking strange after the change.

15:47.144 --> 15:48.345
- It's the last day.
- Hungry?

15:48.345 --> 15:51.364
- It's hard for me to part.
- A little bit.

15:52.345 --> 15:55.485
Speaking of which,
it's hardest for me to part.

15:55.485 --> 16:00.324
It's rare to have such an event
where all you big shots get together.

16:00.324 --> 16:04.626
Our flight is early tomorrow morning.
It's 1 PM now.

16:05.246 --> 16:09.625
Though it's a nice day with great views,
no need to say goodbye so early, right?

16:09.625 --> 16:16.525
- More emotional than voice actors.
- We need to be understanding.

16:16.525 --> 16:19.345
- The cue for music now.
- The emotion time.

16:19.345 --> 16:23.264
- Look.
- You never understand my tenderness.

16:23.264 --> 16:27.605
Alright, I'll hold it in, okay?
Let's go on the bus.

16:32.864 --> 16:35.465
What are you staring at?
Not leaving and being naughty?

16:35.465 --> 16:39.465
All the cars here are chartered. If you
don't leave, there will be no cars left.

16:39.518 --> 16:44.025
You're too emotional.
It's 1 PM, and we haven't even eaten.

16:44.025 --> 16:48.545
Another 2-hour ride before we eat
will make us never visit you again.

16:48.545 --> 16:52.946
I've arranged the restaurant.
You made me forget. Let's have lunch.

16:53.025 --> 16:54.225
- Let's go.
- Thanks, Mr. Zhu.

16:54.225 --> 16:56.705
- Let's go this way.
- Go.

16:56.705 --> 16:59.205
Mr. Zhu, you're very considerate.

17:01.344 --> 17:02.930
I am starving.

17:03.262 --> 17:04.125
So hot.

17:04.125 --> 17:08.104
- You took so long to get two bottles?
- I can't stand the thirst anymore.

17:08.104 --> 17:11.104
Not for drinking. It's for washing
tableware. You still don't know it?

17:11.104 --> 17:12.834
- You don't know it?
- Silly.

17:12.834 --> 17:14.385
I was just about to do it.

17:14.385 --> 17:16.265
- Wash it for me.
- Muddleheaded.

17:16.265 --> 17:20.005
- What are the specialties here?
- Waitress, the menu.

17:20.005 --> 17:25.125
You've eaten almost everything. The rice
in bamboo tubes here is the best.

17:25.125 --> 17:26.505
So I brought you here today.

17:26.505 --> 17:27.705
The rice in bamboo tubes.

17:27.705 --> 17:32.985
This is all cooked on the fire.
There's both regular and glutinous rice.

17:32.985 --> 17:39.825
Many flavors, pickled bamboo shoots,
chopped beef, oil tofu, smoked meat.

17:39.825 --> 17:41.865
- There are many.
- One of each flavor.

17:41.865 --> 17:46.245
- I think this is tasty.
- I'd like to try a bit of each dish.

17:46.245 --> 17:48.804
Osmanthus wine.

17:49.985 --> 17:54.105
- Right. It should be paired with wine.
- To pair with the rice and...

17:54.105 --> 17:56.605
- Stir-fried bamboo shoots with eggs.
- Mr. Qiang.

17:56.605 --> 17:57.884
You understand too well.

17:57.884 --> 18:02.504
The fresh bamboo shoots were just dug up
from the mountain after the rain.

18:02.504 --> 18:09.165
No other place has such fresh shoots.
Crisp, sweet and refreshing.

18:09.945 --> 18:13.764
If you stir-fry it with some eggs,
it'll be even tenderer than eggs.

18:15.304 --> 18:17.965
Zhu, you might as well become
a food vlogger as a side job.

18:17.965 --> 18:22.885
These two would make the best team.
One cooks and one eats.

18:22.885 --> 18:28.784
I'm busy managing my large business.
Usually, it's my secretary's duty.

18:28.784 --> 18:32.524
If it weren't for our friendship,
you wouldn't even be able to see me.

18:32.524 --> 18:34.905
- Getting cocky.
- Putting on airs.

18:34.905 --> 18:37.744
- Keep your back straight when you talk.
- Yes.

18:37.744 --> 18:41.205
He used to insist on tipping me
when listening to my live-stream.

18:41.205 --> 18:44.005
- He's being shy.
- You're exposing someone's past.

18:44.005 --> 18:46.725
- His filter was too strong back then.
- Stop it.

18:46.725 --> 18:48.485
You start to sweat. Look.

18:48.485 --> 18:52.905
How about this?
I'll order two of each flavor

18:52.905 --> 18:54.845
- for you all, okay?
- Okay.

18:54.845 --> 18:56.344
- Wait a moment. It's okay.
- Thank you.

18:56.344 --> 18:57.725
You drink so fast.

18:58.705 --> 19:02.485
You're always making fun of him.
Is he really the biggest sponsor?

19:03.425 --> 19:05.284
His business is doing quite well.

19:05.945 --> 19:10.725
When we first met at a restaurant, he
entered and said he owned a share of it.

19:10.725 --> 19:14.285
We all thought it was a joke, but then
the owner came over to greet us!

19:14.285 --> 19:15.025
We are shocked.

19:15.025 --> 19:17.965
And back then he was really shy.
You couldn't tell at all.

19:17.965 --> 19:21.205
- Right. Not like now.
- What about me now?

19:21.205 --> 19:24.385
You gave me a fright.
Speak of the devil.

19:24.385 --> 19:28.464
- Only these dishes now?
- How could I not be shy? All big shots.

19:28.464 --> 19:31.565
But let me tell you.
This is what's interesting online.

19:31.565 --> 19:35.305
No matter in your everyday life,
how rich you are or what you look like,

19:35.305 --> 19:38.745
if you want others to respect you,
you must be capable, right?

19:38.745 --> 19:40.705
- Right.
- Well said.

19:40.705 --> 19:43.485
- I'll go have a look.
- Hurry up.

19:44.504 --> 19:45.685
Give it a taste.

19:47.824 --> 19:50.085
- What's there to choose from?
- She says this is delicious.

19:50.085 --> 19:54.145
- Here's the rice in bamboo tubes.
- Considerate.

19:54.145 --> 19:57.638
- Great! Put them here.
- Hot.

19:57.662 --> 19:59.558
- Take away the plates.
- The dishes.

19:59.582 --> 20:00.545
Here are all the dishes.

20:00.545 --> 20:02.225
- Spin it to eat what you want.
- Alright.

20:02.225 --> 20:03.486
- We have the same.
- This is minced meat.

20:03.486 --> 20:05.324
- The same.
- We have the same.

20:05.945 --> 20:07.405
I'll try mine.

20:13.744 --> 20:15.764
So good. This is glutinous rice.

20:16.385 --> 20:18.925
- Try this. It's made with rice.
- Okay.

20:19.705 --> 20:20.925
Rice.

20:25.625 --> 20:26.925
It's also good.

20:27.584 --> 20:29.445
- Try this.
- Okay.

20:33.824 --> 20:35.284
Fresh and sweet.

20:37.344 --> 20:40.645
I plan to read some food-related books
and learn more words later.

20:40.645 --> 20:45.564
Otherwise, I can only say
it's delicious and fresh.

20:46.225 --> 20:47.405
That's fine too.

20:51.185 --> 20:52.025
What are you laughing at?

20:52.025 --> 20:54.344
Zhu, you used to be quite shy.
Why are you like this now?

20:54.344 --> 20:56.345
- What's wrong with me?
- Perform a shy act for everyone.

20:56.345 --> 20:59.905
- Do it.
- I'm too old for that.

20:59.905 --> 21:02.965
Zhu, I'll toast you.

21:09.304 --> 21:11.244
Thanks for your hard work this time.

21:11.985 --> 21:16.244
- An honor to have Mr. Qiang's toast.
- Thank you.

21:17.385 --> 21:18.685
You drank it all?

21:19.425 --> 21:21.224
- High tolerance.
- High tolerance.

21:21.224 --> 21:22.604
Another glass.

21:24.024 --> 21:27.165
It was a public performance yesterday.
Today, it's for us.

21:27.165 --> 21:30.385
- Here's to our own tenth anniversary.
- Cheers.

21:30.385 --> 21:33.344
- To our tenth anniversary.
- To our tenth anniversary.

21:33.344 --> 21:36.165
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

21:43.344 --> 21:46.844
You overate again.
I told you to eat slower.

21:47.625 --> 21:50.604
For the last night,
I've booked a villa suite for you.

21:52.584 --> 22:00.584
The beautiful scenery, the river
and the green mountains, and the villa.

22:01.264 --> 22:03.585
- It's out of date, Zhu.
- No, it's not.

22:03.585 --> 22:05.705
Let me tell you something, Sheng.

22:05.705 --> 22:10.245
Zhu knows we are leaving tomorrow.
He booked a villa suite for us to party.

22:10.245 --> 22:11.465
Reserved for you.

22:11.465 --> 22:15.104
- Thank you, Mr. Zhu.
- Thank you, Mr. Zhu.

22:15.104 --> 22:18.005
Don't mention it.
You gave it up yourself.

22:18.005 --> 22:22.285
- It's our last day, after all.
- Thank you, Mr. Zhu.

22:22.285 --> 22:25.505
- Is one enough?
- No.

22:25.505 --> 22:28.304
- One room per person.
- We want two more rooms.

22:28.304 --> 22:32.604
- Quite quiet here.
- Let's turn here.

22:34.104 --> 22:37.685
- Let's go. What do you think?
- Magnificent.

22:39.744 --> 22:40.925
Have a look.

22:41.784 --> 22:44.104
- It's by the river.
- And a yard too.

22:44.104 --> 22:47.265
- This is really good.
- Come and take a look.

22:47.265 --> 22:49.385
- Look over there.
- It lifts our spirits.

22:49.385 --> 22:53.465
- We can have a barbecue at night.
- The water is suitable for swimming.

22:53.465 --> 22:56.365
- The tea set is nice too.
- All of these are particularly good.

22:57.024 --> 22:58.825
- Let's play mahjong.
- Okay, I'll get the mahjong set.

22:58.825 --> 23:01.385
- Anyone up for playing mahjong?
- Me!

23:01.385 --> 23:03.205
- Sheng, I'm heading over there.
- Let's go.

23:03.205 --> 23:06.524
- Where did you find it?
- Mahjong.

23:08.945 --> 23:11.565
- Let's go out for a walk.
- Where are we going?

23:11.565 --> 23:15.965
- The West Street. Go tidy up first.
- Okay.

23:18.865 --> 23:19.925
Come on.

23:21.024 --> 23:23.250
Smile. Be happier.

23:23.870 --> 23:26.125
- Handsome.
- Make sure to get the sun in the photo.

23:26.125 --> 23:28.645
- Of course.
- Let me check it out.

23:30.145 --> 23:33.365
The scenery is so beautiful.
I really don't want to leave.

23:33.985 --> 23:38.324
- How about we open a restaurant here?
- I refuse. I want to pursue my career.

23:38.905 --> 23:40.445
I'm not giving you the picture.

23:44.344 --> 23:49.105
- Where are you two going? Together.
- Are you trying to be a third wheel?

23:49.105 --> 23:51.282
If it rains, I can hold
an umbrella for them.

23:51.486 --> 23:54.765
- Where are you going?
- The West Street. You can come join us.

23:54.765 --> 23:57.604
- Alright
- Let's go.

24:00.665 --> 24:03.885
- Which place do you want to go to?
- Hurry up.

24:05.625 --> 24:06.955
Look at this.

24:08.190 --> 24:10.605
Catch it.

24:10.605 --> 24:13.664
- A piglet.
- So cute.

24:13.664 --> 24:15.925
- Don't run.
- Help them!

24:16.705 --> 24:18.604
- Come on.
- Feishao, you fool. Stop there.

24:19.225 --> 24:20.665
- So clumsy.
- Should we go help them?

24:20.665 --> 24:26.465
- Chase. It can run so fast.
- Hurry to the back.

24:26.465 --> 24:30.165
- Why are you so clumsy? Together.
- Just block for me. Won't that do?

24:30.165 --> 24:32.850
- I take the left. You take the right.
- Alright. Come on.

24:36.865 --> 24:40.125
You're so skilled.
It seems to like you a lot.

24:41.344 --> 24:44.365
- Thank you very much.
- You're welcome.

24:45.905 --> 24:50.985
Really? Even animals can't resist you!

24:50.985 --> 24:53.885
That's what he gets.
Not something you can have.

24:54.784 --> 24:58.585
Can I go to another department?
He disses me every day.

24:58.585 --> 25:01.324
Go ahead, but there'll be
even more people dissing you.

25:03.625 --> 25:08.445
The sharp-tongued ones, Zhou Zheng
and Feng Yasong. Real headache.

25:19.064 --> 25:22.104
- It's really hot.
- There are quite a few tea shops.

25:22.104 --> 25:24.347
They have
handmade brittle candies there.

25:24.371 --> 25:26.145
(Zhuang Handmade Brittle Candies)

25:26.145 --> 25:30.184
Let's go buy some. Some people in studio
didn't come due to some family matters.

25:30.184 --> 25:33.125
- I'll buy some specialties for them.
- I'll buy some for my family too.

25:33.125 --> 25:36.424
- One of my roommates is your fan.
- May I try it?

25:36.424 --> 25:37.725
- Try any.
- Really?

25:39.145 --> 25:40.405
It's quite pretty.

25:40.405 --> 25:42.965
- Let's have a taste first.
- Okay.

25:48.414 --> 25:49.618
Is it tasty?

25:50.264 --> 25:52.384
Yeah, very tasty.

25:52.384 --> 25:56.284
- How much is the osmanthus cake?
- 28 for a box which contains 20 pieces.

25:56.824 --> 25:59.125
- I'd like ten bags.
- Okay.

25:59.125 --> 26:02.884
- Take some home as well.
- You're so generous?

26:02.884 --> 26:07.545
Thank you two for helping Sheng
accomplish her first live performance

26:07.545 --> 26:11.025
that created a record
with millions of people watching.

26:11.025 --> 26:14.585
Going by what you said, we should
buy something for Shengshengman.

26:14.585 --> 26:17.685
- After all, she did backing vocals.
- Thanks for offering such timely help.

26:17.685 --> 26:21.885
You'll have plenty of chances
to thank her, but now it's my chance.

26:24.024 --> 26:26.084
- Cut the formality.
- Alright.

26:26.665 --> 26:27.865
Let's go and have a look over there.

26:27.865 --> 26:29.344
- Is that tasty?
- It's quite tasty.

26:29.344 --> 26:31.704
- What flavor is this?
- It's rose-flavored.

26:31.704 --> 26:33.704
- Try some.
- This tastes good.

26:33.704 --> 26:35.525
- Ten bags, please.
- Okay.

26:35.525 --> 26:36.725
Try this.

26:37.465 --> 26:40.445
Our local specialty has been around
since the Qing Dynasty.

26:41.225 --> 26:43.944
- This one is a must-buy.
- Then ten bags of this too.

26:43.944 --> 26:45.125
Okay.

26:49.385 --> 26:50.385
You eat.

26:52.865 --> 26:54.244
Like matcha-flavored one?

26:58.784 --> 26:59.925
Come here.

27:01.544 --> 27:05.185
- It's early to stroll around here.
- Yes, and the shops ahead seem similar.

27:05.185 --> 27:07.564
- Really?
- Is this okay?

27:08.344 --> 27:11.004
This is the place where we are gonna
show gratitude to you.

27:13.625 --> 27:17.444
- How is it?
- You're embarrassing me.

27:17.444 --> 27:22.485
Just relax. He's just using you
as an excuse to drink.

27:23.185 --> 27:25.205
- I'll go check for a table inside.
- Okay.

27:25.205 --> 27:29.324
- You guys drink. I won't.
- Can you drink?

27:29.945 --> 27:34.125
- I can try a little.
- Then drink a little. Let's go.

27:34.985 --> 27:36.725
- Just put it here.
- Come on.

27:37.544 --> 27:38.925
A soft drink.

27:40.064 --> 27:41.524
- Go.
- Go.

27:43.504 --> 27:44.784
- The menu, please.
- Wait a moment.

27:44.784 --> 27:47.164
- Sheng, do you drink alcohol normally?
- Let me look.

27:47.164 --> 27:52.284
To tell the truth, I'm very grateful.
Only you can handle him.

27:54.185 --> 28:00.084
You're more like good friends
than a couple.

28:01.705 --> 28:04.284
Do you feel shy because you just
started your relationship?

28:06.078 --> 28:07.794
What would you like to drink?

28:08.425 --> 28:09.564
Fine.

28:11.230 --> 28:15.084
Hello, five of these, please.

28:27.774 --> 28:29.084
The same.

28:30.590 --> 28:33.906
(Yitian West Street)

28:42.206 --> 28:45.304
- Cheers.
- May our studio get better and better.

28:45.304 --> 28:46.844
Don't drink too fast.

28:53.665 --> 28:57.445
He said he wouldn't drink but ended up
being drunk like this again.

28:59.198 --> 29:02.565
- Should we take him to...
- Alright. I'll take him to throw up.

29:02.565 --> 29:05.965
Feishao, it's time to go on stage.

29:06.744 --> 29:09.944
- Which song to sing?
- White Horse into Reed. Let's go.

29:09.944 --> 29:11.565
I'll take you to the stage.

29:11.565 --> 29:13.345
- Can you do it on your own?
- Yes, it's alright.

29:13.345 --> 29:15.145
- Come on. Take it slow.
- Be careful.

29:15.145 --> 29:17.324
Lean on me. Let's go.

29:21.264 --> 29:23.165
This is hawthorn-flavored.

29:24.104 --> 29:26.564
I've noticed
that you can hold your liquor well.

29:28.544 --> 29:32.044
Nobody can tell if I'm drunk.

29:34.185 --> 29:38.565
- Are you now?
- Not now.

29:38.565 --> 29:44.045
If I am, I'll say a lot of words.

29:44.045 --> 29:51.285
I'll be blunt, and others can't tell.
And I'll say whatever I want to say.

29:51.285 --> 29:53.244
What do you want to say now?

30:03.262 --> 30:04.604
Did you intend

30:06.001 --> 30:07.460
to kiss me on the day

30:09.200 --> 30:10.700
of the performance?

30:30.521 --> 30:31.821
What do you think?

30:34.561 --> 30:36.581
I think

30:37.761 --> 30:38.761
that it is.

30:41.440 --> 30:43.900
If you say so, then it is.

30:44.680 --> 30:48.341
I'm asking you. You should answer me.

30:52.920 --> 30:55.821
It really smells like hawthorn.

31:14.200 --> 31:15.420
Now?

31:16.081 --> 31:17.180
No.

31:19.160 --> 31:21.900
Of course not in public.

31:30.561 --> 31:32.900
- Is he okay?
- Yeah, he just threw up.

31:33.440 --> 31:38.421
- You carry Feishao. I pay the bill.
- No way. My treat.

31:38.421 --> 31:42.834
How can I let you pay for my first time
drinking with my girlfriend?

31:43.198 --> 31:45.081
Fine, you always have a reason.

31:45.081 --> 31:47.700
Stand properly.

31:48.561 --> 31:51.620
Let me carry the bag.
Wait a moment. Okay.

31:53.081 --> 31:56.680
- Pick up the things.
- Here you go.

31:56.680 --> 31:59.221
- Then we're heading outside slowly.
- Okay.

31:59.221 --> 32:00.860
- You guys hurry up.
- Okay.

32:11.960 --> 32:13.821
Do you want to drink more?

32:14.680 --> 32:17.458
- Want more to drink?
- No.

32:18.078 --> 32:22.180
Aren't we waiting for Wang Ke to return?
When they return, we will leave.

32:24.120 --> 32:25.120
Right.

32:39.241 --> 32:42.066
(You guys go ahead and call a ride back.
I will wait a little longer.)

32:44.041 --> 32:46.660
Alright. Then we'll go back.

32:51.200 --> 32:55.801
With such a low tolerance,
why were you bragging?

32:55.801 --> 33:00.721
- We can't get a cab here.
- Let me sing a song for you.

33:00.721 --> 33:04.301
No. Carrying you is embarrassing enough.
Please don't sing. I'm begging you.

33:04.301 --> 33:12.521
Silver bowl filled with snow,
bright moon hides the heron.

33:12.521 --> 33:16.541
Sing but hold on tight,
or you'll fall off.

33:16.541 --> 33:20.620
Sounds of the flute. Travelers...

33:28.321 --> 33:32.341
- Why haven't they come back yet?
- They've already left.

33:33.241 --> 33:34.581
They've gone back?

33:36.801 --> 33:39.460
- Are you sober now?
- I'm not drunk.

33:41.561 --> 33:45.521
- The drink was good. Did you have some?
- Yes, I did.

33:45.521 --> 33:50.520
Why did they leave? Who will take
our candies now that they have left?

33:50.520 --> 33:53.100
- Don't worry. Be careful.
- The candies...

33:54.400 --> 33:55.460
Are you alright?

33:59.801 --> 34:01.020
This is not right.

34:04.400 --> 34:07.661
It should be like this.

34:12.040 --> 34:13.040
Okay.

34:16.480 --> 34:19.101
- Let's go this way.
- Right.

34:22.601 --> 34:25.940
- Can I ask you a question?
- Go ahead.

34:29.121 --> 34:30.460
Do I look good?

34:52.201 --> 34:53.701
Yes, undoubtedly.

35:11.960 --> 35:13.301
I think so too.

35:26.721 --> 35:27.721
Your turn.

35:30.080 --> 35:31.861
- South Wind.
- A good hand.

35:31.861 --> 35:32.940
- A bad hand.
- Three of bamboo.

35:32.940 --> 35:34.801
- Pong.
- Pong.

35:34.801 --> 35:36.881
- You can't tell her.
- You can see both of their tiles.

35:36.881 --> 35:39.561
- She can't play. Can't I help her?
- Play it yourself.

35:39.561 --> 35:40.581
- Who?
- Open the door.

35:40.581 --> 35:41.621
Who is there?

35:42.400 --> 35:43.940
- Open the door.
- Hurry up. Pong or not?

35:43.940 --> 35:46.040
- Help him.
- Who is it?

35:46.040 --> 35:47.560
- What happened?
- Did he get beaten up?

35:47.560 --> 35:51.000
- He's just drunk. Give a hand, now.
- How much did he drink?

35:51.000 --> 35:52.101
Come on.

35:52.101 --> 35:55.121
- Take him into the room.
- No, don't go inside the room.

35:55.121 --> 35:57.761
- White sheets. Put him on the couch.
- The couch.

35:57.761 --> 35:58.960
- How stingy you are.
- Be careful.

35:58.960 --> 36:00.940
Wait. His head.

36:01.841 --> 36:05.321
- A couple's suite ended up like this.
- He fell down.

36:05.321 --> 36:07.720
- How much did he drink?
- Not much.

36:07.720 --> 36:12.421
- Didn't Mr. Mo go with you?
- They went to somewhere else.

36:12.421 --> 36:15.281
- Somewhere else?
- To bask in the moonlight.

36:15.281 --> 36:18.741
- Share the local specialties later on.
- Basking in the moonlight.

36:18.741 --> 36:23.520
- Leave some for Xiaoxing and Sheng.
- Including me?

36:23.520 --> 36:26.060
They were bought
by your roommate's boyfriend.

36:26.681 --> 36:31.321
- Mr. Qiang is so nice.
- He has a truly high EQ.

36:31.321 --> 36:32.781
- Let me take a look.
- Look later.

36:32.781 --> 36:35.241
- Continue to play.
- Come on. Whose turn was it just now?

36:35.241 --> 36:36.841
- The three of bamboo.
- Pong or not?

36:36.841 --> 36:38.940
- Pong.
- You need to flip it out.

36:40.601 --> 36:44.500
I started practicing the piano
four hours every day as a kid.

36:45.480 --> 36:50.160
I cried and even ran away from home,
but my parents never gave in.

36:50.160 --> 36:55.581
Later, when I was upset, I could easily
play and compose a piece of music.

36:55.581 --> 36:57.621
I started being truly grateful
to my parents.

36:58.681 --> 37:00.781
- Be careful.
- Think about it.

37:00.781 --> 37:06.121
If I didn't learn it, I couldn't compose
and I wouldn't be Shengshengman.

37:06.121 --> 37:11.740
If I weren't Shengshengman,
I wouldn't have joined online clubs,

37:11.740 --> 37:15.261
- nor would I've had my voice chat room.
- Be careful.

37:16.601 --> 37:27.121
I also wouldn't have chatted
with Xiaoxing in the room that morning

37:28.360 --> 37:29.440
and then met you.

37:29.440 --> 37:36.434
- So I should thank my parents, right?
- Right.

37:39.000 --> 37:43.821
Why were you
in my voice chat room that day?

37:44.841 --> 37:46.060
You want to know?

37:51.040 --> 37:53.020
At first, I was wondering too.

37:57.321 --> 38:03.741
Wondering why I suddenly had
some spare time and was browsing online.

38:04.801 --> 38:06.860
Wondering

38:08.121 --> 38:09.860
why I just happened

38:10.520 --> 38:12.741
to enter your voice chat room.

38:14.480 --> 38:16.101
Aren't you happy about it?

38:18.480 --> 38:20.341
An unexpected delight.

38:22.400 --> 38:24.060
Yeah.

38:25.440 --> 38:26.781
Why?

38:29.161 --> 38:30.341
It's destined.

38:35.360 --> 38:38.900
- Young man, over here.
- Coming.

38:42.321 --> 38:47.921
- The hot tea and blanket are all ready.
- Okay, thank you.

38:47.921 --> 38:52.580
- What are these preparations for?
- A night cruise on the Lijiang River.

38:55.040 --> 38:58.380
- We have a flight tomorrow morning.
- I know.

38:59.080 --> 39:02.130
With me here, you can rest assured.

39:02.686 --> 39:04.781
Did you forget who woke you up that day?

39:06.880 --> 39:07.941
Let's go.

39:08.681 --> 39:09.821
Be careful.

39:12.201 --> 39:13.701
Slow down.

39:15.520 --> 39:18.261
Put on this life jacket.

39:32.960 --> 39:33.960
Sit.

39:41.880 --> 39:45.741
- All set, sir.
- Okay, let's sail.

39:48.761 --> 39:52.741
- Isn't there an engine?
- He was afraid it'd be too noisy

39:53.360 --> 39:58.180
and asked me if there is another way
to propel the bamboo raft.

39:58.180 --> 40:04.561
In the era without engines,
didn't people use poles to paddle?

40:04.561 --> 40:07.380
- Thanks for your hard work.
- Hang on.

40:13.758 --> 40:15.102
- I have drawn it.
- You won again.

40:15.102 --> 40:19.960
- How come you always win?
- I must have a lucky star.

40:19.960 --> 40:22.621
With you by my side, I keep winning.

40:25.040 --> 40:26.241
Look at yourself.

40:26.241 --> 40:31.021
What's wrong? I'm a lucky star,
but I didn't cheat, so why the stare?

40:31.021 --> 40:36.020
- You do have some integrity.
- Yes, businessmen care about Fengshui.

40:36.020 --> 40:38.141
Those who have a thriving business
are seen as lucky stars.

40:38.141 --> 40:41.041
I don't like what you're saying.
I'm a businessman too. Why didn't I win?

40:41.041 --> 40:43.900
Because he's more powerful than you.

40:46.281 --> 40:50.641
- Is there any water?
- No. The water's been cut off.

40:50.641 --> 40:56.581
- Your logistics are getting worse.
- Look how drunk he is.

40:56.581 --> 40:58.398
- Focus on tiles.
- He's forgotten we're in Yangshuo.

40:58.398 --> 41:01.580
- Come on. Continue.
- Here's a bottle of water.

41:10.641 --> 41:12.500
It's so comfortable here.

41:13.880 --> 41:15.101
It's very quiet.

41:27.601 --> 41:34.461
The water here is shallow and safe.
Take your time and appreciate the view.

41:34.461 --> 41:36.781
If you're tired, just sleep.

41:37.841 --> 41:38.900
Thank you.

42:08.560 --> 42:14.781
The osmanthus-flavored food I've eaten
these days makes me smell like it.

42:22.737 --> 42:27.845
♪ There is a voice
that soaks the green plums ♪

42:28.689 --> 42:33.637
♪ There is a voice
that wrinkles the blue sky ♪

42:34.567 --> 42:38.856
♪ Shedding an invisible spring rain ♪

42:38.856 --> 42:45.055
♪ The world is drunk at a timid moment ♪

42:46.381 --> 42:51.749
♪ We talk and laugh
as if we are holding hands ♪

42:52.689 --> 42:58.737
♪ We stay silent
like falling behind the sunset ♪

42:58.737 --> 43:02.833
♪ That moment is still lingering ♪

43:02.833 --> 43:09.190
♪ When our eyes meet,
all vanish into nothing ♪

43:35.409 --> 43:41.955
♪ You flow through my heart like a river ♪

43:42.129 --> 43:47.717
♪ Echoing with the constant gentleness
of the bright moon ♪

43:48.017 --> 43:51.185
♪ Looking back
among fleeting and everlasting moments ♪

43:51.185 --> 43:54.169
♪ We embrace as we look around ♪

43:54.193 --> 43:59.429
♪ Each sound is a promise of forever
to a lifetime ♪

43:59.537 --> 44:05.989
♪ You linger in my dreams
countless times ♪

44:06.129 --> 44:11.441
♪ Whenever I see you,
my heart flutters a thousand times ♪

44:11.441 --> 44:15.282
♪ Birds fly past spring and autumn
once again ♪

44:15.282 --> 44:18.778
♪ The splendid world still remains ♪

44:18.890 --> 44:22.577
♪ Gifting us freedom ♪

44:22.577 --> 44:27.496
♪ We ferment each other into wine ♪

44:28.682 --> 44:34.681
♪ Within the intoxication, I can feel ♪

